Failure Group cuts outlook for Q4 . The Failure Group , which reported lower third - quarter earnings on Tuesday , also said it had lowered its expectations for the fourth quarter . The company - - an engineering consultancy that investigates equipment failures , said third - quarter net income fell to $ 0 . 06 a share from $ 0 . 09 in the same period last year . The drop reflected a slowdown in litigation projects at its Phoenix test facility and declining usage of its computer and database services , it said . " With the slowdown in Phoenix expected to continue for the duration of 1996 , we have reduced our outlook for the fourth quarter , " the company said . Officials were not immediately available to elaborate on its fourth - quarter forecast . 
